&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;From the series &lt;cite class="series"&gt;The Iron Seas&lt;/cite&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;cite&gt;The Iron Duke&lt;/cite&gt;, by Meljean Brook; copyright 2010 by Melissa Kahn;
ISBN 978-0-425-23667-3.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;cite&gt;Heart of Steel&lt;/cite&gt;, by Meljean Brook; copyright 2011 by Melissa
Kahn; ISB 978-0-425-24330-5.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From the front cover: «“Meljean Brook has brilliantly defined he
new genre of steampunk romance.” — Jayne Ann Krentz, &lt;cite&gt;New York
Times&lt;/cite&gt; bestselling author».&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are very good.  The back covers list them as “paranormal
romance” &lt;a class="footnote-reference brackets" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/13/meljean-brook/#pr-section" id="id1"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;, but I suspect that they form exemplars for
a new genre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Her setting is interestingly and greatly altered history.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stories by Meljean Brook appear in (at least) the following
anthologies: &lt;cite&gt;Hot Spell&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Wild Thing&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;First Blood&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Must
Love Hellhounds&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Burning Up&lt;/cite&gt;, and &lt;cite&gt;Angels of Darkness&lt;/cite&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- Explicit sex: clit, cock --&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;dl class="footnote brackets"&gt;
&lt;dt class="label" id="pr-section"&gt;&lt;span class="brackets"&gt;&lt;a class="fn-backref" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/13/meljean-brook/#id1"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;&lt;p&gt;The local library I frequent most often has a
separate section for paranormal romance now, though these were
shelved in general fiction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;/dl&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>action</category><category>recent reading</category><category>romance</category><category>steampunk</category><guid>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/13/meljean-brook/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 14 Jun 2012 04:34:33 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Recent Reading: Laurell K. Hamilton</title><link>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/12/laurell-k-hamilton/</link><dc:creator>T. Kurt Bond</dc:creator><description>&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;cite&gt;Kiss the Dead&lt;/cite&gt;, by Laurell K. Hamilton, copyright 2012;
ISBN 978-0-425-24754-9.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;cite class="series"&gt;Anita Blake, Vampire Hunter&lt;/cite&gt; novel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I haven't read &lt;cite&gt;Hit List&lt;/cite&gt; yet, but it is on the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description><category>action</category><category>modern</category><category>paranormal</category><category>recent reading</category><category>romance</category><category>supernatural</category><category>thriller</category><guid>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/12/laurell-k-hamilton/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 Jun 2012 20:16:26 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Recent Reading: Lynn Viehl</title><link>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/10/lynn-viehl/</link><dc:creator>T. Kurt Bond</dc:creator><description>&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;cite&gt;Nightshine&lt;/cite&gt;, by Lynn Viehl; copyright 2011 by Sheila Kelly;
ISBN 978-0-451-41314-7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part of the &lt;cite class="series"&gt;Kindred&lt;/cite&gt; series, which also includes
&lt;cite&gt;Shadowlight&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Dreamveil&lt;/cite&gt;, and &lt;cite&gt;Frostfire&lt;/cite&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I gather the &lt;cite class="series"&gt;Darkyn&lt;/cite&gt; series is related.  It includes at
least &lt;cite&gt;If Angels Burn&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Private Demons&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Dark Need&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Night Lost&lt;/cite&gt;,
&lt;cite&gt;Evermore&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Twilight Full&lt;/cite&gt;, and &lt;cite&gt;Stay the Night&lt;/cite&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description><category>paranormal</category><category>recent reading</category><category>romance</category><guid>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/10/lynn-viehl/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 10 Jun 2012 22:35:57 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Recent Reading: Karen Chance</title><link>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/05/09/karen-chance/</link><dc:creator>T. Kurt Bond</dc:creator><description>&lt;ul&gt;
